{
  "explanation": "The defendant committed a serious breach of trust by embezzling $25,000 from their employer. However, several mitigating factors must be considered: the defendant has no prior criminal record, and they have already made partial restitution of the stolen funds. The courtroom outburst calling for a ten-year sentence holds no legal weight and is entirely disproportionate to the severity of this first-time white-collar offense. Balancing the need for accountability with the defendant's lack of criminal history and efforts to make amends, a brief period of incarceration is warranted to impress upon the defendant the seriousness of the crime, followed by a period of probation to ensure full restitution is paid.",
  "verdict": 6
}
